# PRF SuperApp API - Cline Rules

## Stack

- PHP 8.5.2, Laravel 12, Filament v5, Livewire v4, Sanctum v4
- Pest v4 (testing), Pint v1 (formatting), Tailwind CSS v4
- Spatie QueryBuilder, Activity Log, Media Library, Permissions
- Frontend bundling: Bun (`bun run build` / `bun run dev`)

---

## Request Flow

```
HTTP Request ‚Üí Route (routes/api/v1.php) ‚Üí Controller (app/Http/Controllers/API/)
  ‚Üí Form Request (app/Http/Requests/{Domain}/) ‚Üí Job::dispatchSync() (app/Jobs/{Domain}/)
  ‚Üí Model + Observers ‚Üí API Resource (app/Http/Resources/{Domain}/) ‚Üí JSON Response
```

---

## Architecture Rules

### Controllers
- Lightweight - delegate ALL business logic to Jobs via `dispatchSync()`
- Use `Spatie\QueryBuilder\QueryBuilder` for filtering/includes
- Return API Resources for all responses
- Look up records by ULID, not ID (no implicit route model binding)

### Jobs (Business Logic)
- Location: `app/Jobs/{Domain}/` (e.g., `CreateJob.php`, `UpdateJob.php`)
- Use `Dispatchable` trait, constructor property promotion
- Convert ULIDs to IDs for foreign keys inside the job
- Return the created/updated model

### Models
- Use `HasUlid`, `HasFactory`, `LogsActivity`, `SoftDeletes` traits
- Define `INCLUDES` constant for QueryBuilder eager loading
- Use `casts()` method (not `$casts` property)
- Use return type hints on all relationships
- Register Observers with `#[ObservedBy()]` attribute

### Form Requests
- Location: `app/Http/Requests/{Domain}/` (e.g., `CreateRequest.php`)
- Always use Form Request classes - never inline validation
- Use array-based validation rules
- Use `exists:table,column` for ULID validation

### API Resources
- Location: `app/Http/Resources/{Domain}/Resource.php`
- Always include `'entity' => 'resource_name'` field
- Expose ULID, never ID
- Use `whenLoaded()` for relationships
- Use `->value` for enum values

### Enums
- Location: `app/Enums/`
- Integer-backed, SCREAMING_CASE keys
- Include `getValues()`, `getOptions()`, `getLabel()`, `getColor()` helpers

### Routes
- Location: `routes/api/v1.php`, `routes/api/v2.php`
- Use `auth:sanctum` middleware
- ULID string parameters (not route model binding)
- Group by resource with prefix and named routes

---

## Coding Conventions

### PHP
- Always use curly braces for control structures, even single-line
- PHP 8 constructor property promotion in `__construct()`
- Explicit return type declarations on all methods
- PHPDoc blocks over inline comments
- No `env()` outside config files - use `config()` instead
- No `DB::` facade - use `Model::query()` instead
- Prevent N+1 queries with eager loading
- Descriptive names: `isRegisteredForDiscounts`, not `discount()`

### Laravel 12 Structure
- Middleware configured in `bootstrap/app.php` (no `Kernel.php`)
- Console commands auto-discovered from `app/Console/Commands/`
- Providers in `bootstrap/providers.php`

---

## Testing

### Rules
- **Every change must be tested** - write or update a Pest test
- Use Pest syntax exclusively (no PHPUnit class-based tests)
- Tests in `tests/Feature/` (most) and `tests/Unit/`
- Use factories with custom states when available
- Use datasets for validation rule testing
- Use specific assertions: `assertForbidden()` not `assertStatus(403)`

### Commands
```bash
# Run specific file
php artisan test --compact tests/Feature/ExampleTest.php

# Filter by test name
php artisan test --compact --filter=testName

# Run all tests
php artisan test --compact
```

### Formatting
```bash
# Always run before finalizing changes
vendor/bin/pint --dirty
```

---

## New Feature Checklist

1. Create migration
2. Create Model with `HasUlid`, `HasFactory`, `LogsActivity` traits
3. Define `INCLUDES` constant on model
4. Create Factory in `database/factories/`
5. Create API Resource in `app/Http/Resources/{Domain}/Resource.php`
6. Create Form Requests in `app/Http/Requests/{Domain}/`
7. Create Jobs in `app/Jobs/{Domain}/`
8. Create Controller in `app/Http/Controllers/API/`
9. Add routes in `routes/api/v1.php`
10. Create Observer if needed
11. Write Pest tests in `tests/Feature/`

---

## Directory Structure

```
app/
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ Enums/                    # Integer-backed enums
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ Http/
‚îÇ   ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ Controllers/API/      # Lightweight controllers
‚îÇ   ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ Requests/{Domain}/    # Form Request validation
‚îÇ   ‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ Resources/{Domain}/   # API Resources
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ Jobs/{Domain}/            # Business logic
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ Models/                   # Eloquent models (flat)
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ Observers/                # Model lifecycle hooks
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ Policies/                 # Authorization
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ Rules/{Domain}/           # Custom validation rules
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ Services/                 # Shared business logic
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ Events/                   # Domain events
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ Listeners/                # Event listeners
‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ Notifications/            # Notifications

database/
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ factories/
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ migrations/
‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ seeders/

routes/api/
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ v1.php
‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ v2.php
```

---

## Don't

- Don't create new base directories without approval
- Don't change dependencies without approval
- Don't remove tests without approval
- Don't use implicit route model binding (use ULID string params)
- Don't use `DB::` facade (use `Model::query()`)
- Don't use `env()` outside config files
- Don't use inline validation in controllers
- Don't use deprecated Tailwind v3 utilities
